Variation. Length of body of both sexes 6.2-8.0 mm; ovipositor sheath 1.1-1.2 times as long as hind tibia; hind femur more widened in females from Turkey than in holotype, but less so in males from Turkey (about similar to males of 
Gasteruption assectator
); first discal cell of fore wing glabrous and strongly narrowed apically or cell parallel-sided; metasomal sternites (except hypopygium) entirely brownish yellow or largely dark brown; pronotum laterally black or dark brown.
